0Coleman%20Headley%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20born%20as%20Daood%20Sayed%20Gilani%20in%20Washington%20DC%C2%A0to%20Sayed%20Salim%20Gilani%2C%20a%20prominent%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20and%20broadcaster%2C%20and%20his%20American%20wife%2C%20Alice%20Serrill%20Headley.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHeadley%20spent%20his%20early%20years%20at%20a%20boarding%20school%20in%20Pakistan%20before%20moving%20to%20the%20US%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20as%20a%20barman%20at%20his%20family's%20pub%20in%20Philadelphia.%20He%20established%20links%20with%20the%20Pakistan-based%20terror%20group%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%20(LeT).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%201998%2C%20he%20was%20sentenced%20to%20two%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20smuggling%20heroin%20into%20the%20US%20from%20Pakistan.%20Following%20his%20release%2C%20Headley%20began%20working%20with%20the%20US%20Drug%20Enforcement%20Administration%20(DEA)%2C%20carrying%20out%20undercover%20surveillance%20operations%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20attending%20at%20least%20five%20LeT%20training%20camps%20in%20Pakistan%20between%202002%20and%202005%2C%20Headly%20travelled%20to%20India%20on%20the%20instructions%20of%20Lashkar%20commanders%20to%20conduct%20surveillance%2C%20which%20he%20did%20five%20times%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Mumbai%20attacks%20in%202008%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20was%20arrested%20in%202009%20by%20US%20authorities%20before%20he%20could%20carry%20out%20further%20attacks%20in%20Denmark.%20He%20later%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20terrorism%20charges%20and%20cooperated%20with%20investigators%2C%20offering%20detailed%20insights%20into%20LeT%20operations%20and%20Pakistan's%20role.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20is%20serving%20a%2035-year%20prison%20sentence%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20India%20has%20repeatedly%20sought%20his%20extradition%2C%20but%20US%20authorities%20have%20refused%2C%20citing%20his%20cooperation%20deal.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744257180000%2C%