essinsider.com%2Fkids-argentina-have-more-freedom-to-be-themselves-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThey%20didn't%20bat%20an%20eye%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20our%20children%20playing%20right%20next%20to%20us.%20Toto%20pretended%20to%20punch%20Astor.%20Felipe%20got%20sweaty%20and%20red-faced%2C%20running%20around%20to%20avoid%20flying%20fists.%20My%20kid%2C%20Charlie%2C%20well%2C%20I'd%20be%20lying%20if%20I%20said%20he%20wasn't%20acting%20as%20much%20like%20a%20maniac%20and%20a%20monkey%20as%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2296883910-17a9-4ea8-809c-b0145264a2b2%5C%22%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20explain%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Argentina%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-my-kid-to-argentina-for-a-friendlier-school-system-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThis%20would%20never%20fly%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20told%20my%20friends.%20They%20were%20surprised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20kids%20weren't%20violent.%20They%20didn't%20break%20things.%20There%20was%20plenty%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-vs-us-costco-food-court-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espace%20in%20the%20food%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20antics.%20Why%20shouldn't%20they%20be%20able%20to%20play%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20some%20US%20parents%20what%20they%20thought%20about%20letting%20kids%20roughhouse%20in%20public%20spaces%2C%20many%20responded%20with%20anger.%20One%20person%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it's%20not%20your%20living%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20another%20said%20only%20negligent%20parents%20would%20allow%20such%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228ea6e941-b123-4be4-a4be-81c6f3891068%5C%22%3EKids%20are%20part%20of%20life%20in%20Argentina%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20Argentines%20are%20more%20patient%20with%20kids%20because%20they're%20more%20accustomed%20to%20spending%20time%20with%20them.%20Children%20join%20their%20extended%20families%20for%20almost%20every%20occasion%20%E2%80%94%20Sunday%20dinners%2C%20weddings%2C%20parties%2C%20even%20graduations.%20Adults%2C%20babies%2C%20toddlers%2C%20older%20kids%2C%20and%20teens%20spend%20time%20together%20as%20part%20of%20regular%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2010%20years%20old%2C%20Charlie%20is%20more%20comfortable%20with%20babies%20and%20toddlers%20than%20I%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I%20held%20my%20daughter%20Lila%20when%20she%20was%20born%20in%20New%20York%20because%20he's%20been%20around%20younger%20kids%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Argentina%2C%20I've%20eaten%20many%20leisurely%20meals%20in%20restaurants%20while%20my%20kids%20played%20war%20games%20around%20the%20tables%20with%20strangers'%20kids.%20By%20contrast%2C%20worry%20and%20annoyance%20lined%20the%20faces%20of%20people%20in%20restaurants%20when%20we%20took%20our%20toddler%20daughter%20out%20to%20eat%20in%20NYC.%20Luckily%2C%20my%20shy%2C%20sweet%20first%20child%20conducted%20herself%20well%20in%20public%2C%20so%20after%20their%20initial%20upset%2C%20people%20praised%20us%20by%20saying%20how%20quiet%20she%20was%20and%20how%20she%20didn't%20bother%20them%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227bebe24b-a2d2-449d-9a14-fd22cb0f006a%5C%22%3EIn%20New%20York%20a%20stranger%20smacked%20my%20toddler%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20to%20raise%20children%20who%20know%20who%20they%20are%20and%20speak%20up%20for%20what%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%203-year-old%20Lila%2C%20back%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20reached%20out%20a%20tiny%20finger%20to%20touch%20a%20brightly%20colored%20crocheted%20bag%20slung%20on%20the%20shoulder%20of%20the%20woman%20in%20front%20of%20us.%20This%20woman%20felt%20the%20gentle%20pressure%20and%20turned%20around%2C%20smacked%20Lila's%20hand%20away%2C%20and%20screamed%20at%20both%20of%20us%20not%20to%20touch%20her%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20touching%20other%20people's%20things%20is%20inappropriate%